      You’re part of the whānau (family). You’ve signed up for a workshop,
      you’re teaching or directing, you’re one of our crew, you’re a volunteer…
      You get a festival pass, and can come to any and all events during the
      week (note: workshops and shows require that you book but you generally
      have free access!).

